Introductory geology for the non-science major, designed to give a broad, basic understanding of the planet on which we reside, its age and origin, composition and evolution, interrelationships of Earth's major physical systems, scientific revolutions in Earth Science, and the role the physical Earth plays in global politics and economics.

Old styles of command-control are now a thing of the past, except for the most conservative organizations. While good leaders employ a variety of leadership skills and leadership styles to motivate team members, even this is not enough.In addition to traditional leadership traits, Agile leadership emphasizes facilitation and active communication skills. This unique emphasis better positions a leader to lead in a fast paced, impatient, complex environment.The best leaders understand that the leader can no longer stand still, they must be adaptive and nimble. This means new leadership roles and competencies must be practiced that will empower and motivate employees and teams to new levels of productivity. We will explore how to apply agile principles to leadership and the best practices needed to be an effective leader today.

This remote learning lecture-discussion focuses on the relationship between cinema and aesthetic movements in the arts. Films to be screened include Blood of a Poet, The Man Who Fell To Earth, 2001: A Space Odyssey, The Draughtsman's Contract, The Red Shoes, Mulholland Drive, and others. Warning: some films may contain nudity, sexual situations, violence, profanity, substance abuse, and disturbing images.
